{
  "text": "Pulmonary vascular pressure-flow relationships were analyzed using a linear distensible vessel model as described before [CITATION_1] . Briefly, this model describes the vascular pressure-flow characteristic using two parameters: R LIN is interpreted as mean parallel resistance extraalveolar, non-collapsible pulmonary vessels and P ZF as mean critical closing pressure, representing a mean pressure value below a pressure that would not result in a flow in the pulmonary vessels.",
